<h2 id="inst">Instructors</h2>
<h3 id="inst.acctMng">Account Management</h3>
<h4 id="inst.acctMng.instStatus">Obtaining Instructor Status</h4>
If you have an account,
<ol>
  <li>
    Click the <a href="requests.php">Requests</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Change the account type to professor and enter a small amount of text that we can use to verify that you are a professor.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Request Account Type Change</span> link.
  </li>
  <li>
    Your request will be displayed on the page.  Please wait until an administrator can process your request.
  </li>
</ol>
If you do not have an account,
<ol>
  <li>
    Register for an account using the normal form.
  </li>
  <li>
    Check the <span class="underline">Request Professor Status</span> checkbox and enter a small amount of text that we can use to verify that you are a professor.
  </li>
  <li>
    Please wait until an administrator can process your request.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.acctMng.notify">Configure Your E-mail Notification Policy</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Click on the <a href="email_notify_edit.php">E-mail Notifications</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Select the frequency that you want to be sent E-mails.
  </li>
  <li>
    Select the events that you want to receive E-mails for.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the Submit button.
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="inst.courseMng">Course Management</h3>
<h4 id="inst.courseMng.add">Add a Course</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Click on the <a href="courseAddForm.php">Add Course</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Fill in the required information and click the Submit button.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.courseMng.edit">Edit Course Information</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Go to the courses page by clicking the <a href="courses.php">Course Management</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the course you wish to edit and click the pencil icon in the right column.
  </li>
  <li>
    After editing the information, be sure to click the Submit button.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.courseMng.enroll">Enroll Students in a Course</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Go to the courses page by clicking the <a href="courses.php">Course Management</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the course and click the magnifying glass icon in the right column.
  </li>
  <li>
    At the bottom of the page, click the link for <span class="underline">Enroll Additional Students</span>.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the student you wish to enroll and click the <span class="underline">Enroll</span> link next to their name.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.courseMng.drop">Drop Students from a Course</h4>
Please note that this will disassociate all submissions from the course.  This cannot be undone.
<ol>
  <li>
    Go to the courses page by clicking the <a href="courses.php">Course Management</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the course and click the magnifying glass icon in the right column.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the student you wish to drop and click the <span class="underline">Drop Student</span> link next to their name.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.courseMng.dropbox">View Student Dropbox</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Go to the courses page by clicking the <a href="courses.php">Course Management</a> link in the Comtor menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the course and click the magnifying glass icon in the right column.
  </li>
  <li>
    Find the student and click the <span class="underline">View Dropbox</span> link next to their name.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.courseMng.email">Send E-mail to students in a course.</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Select the course from the select box in the top right corner of the page.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">E-mail</span> link in the Modules menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Select the students you wish to send the E-mail to (Hold Ctrl to select multiple students).
  </li>
  <li>
    Fill in the subject and the message and press Submit.
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="inst.assignMng">Assignment Management</h3>
<h4 id="inst.assignMng.add">Add an Assignment</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Select the course from the select box in the top right corner of the page.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Dropbox</span> link in the Modules menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Add New Assignment</span> link at the top of the page.
  </li>
  <li>
    Fill in the name and the open and close dates for the assignment.
  </li>
  <li>
    If you want specific modules to be run, check the checkbox next to the modules to be run.
  </li>
  <li>
    Fill in the grading information and parameters if you do not wish to use the default values.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the Submit button.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.assignMng.edit">Edit an Assignment</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Select the course from the select box in the top right corner of the page.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Dropbox</span> link in the Modules menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Edit</span> link next to the assignment you wish to edit.
  </li>
  <li>
    Edit the assignment information.
  </li>
  <li>
    If you want specific modules to be run, check the checkbox next to the modules to be run.
  </li>
  <li>
    Fill in the grading information and parameters if you do not wish to use the default values. (Note: You may not edit these values if there has already been a submission for this assignment.)
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the Submit button.
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="inst.assignMng.delete">Delete an Assignment</h4>
<ol>
  <li>
    Select the course from the select box in the top right corner of the page.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Dropbox</span> link in the Modules menu to the left.
  </li>
  <li>
    Click the <span class="underline">Delete</span> link next to the assignment you wish to delete. (Note: This will disassociate all reports for this assignment from the course. This cannot be undone.)
  </li>
</ol>
